        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.76-77_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">76</fw>
                
                <opener>
                        Ha Ha Tonka.
                        
                    <dateline>
                        Camdenton, Missouri.
                        December I2, I958.
                    </dateline>
                    
                    Proffesor<sic>Professor</sic> John <hi rend="caps">G</hi> Nieghart.<sic>Neihardt</sic>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Sir-</salute></opener> <p>I know you must be a very busy man, but want you to know how much we enjoy y<del>ur</del><add>ou</add>r program on <hi rend="caps">KOMU TV</hi>. I hope you can excuse this writing as I am no expert with this. If you would be so kind to inform me where I can obtain the book also the map you are reading f<del>t</del><add>r</add>om now I feel that I would be forever in your debt. The wife and both arevery<sic>are very</sic> interested in the Indian History you read about. Both of us have a little War Hoop blood Cherokee and Sauk and Fox with Irish. Neither one of us are educated much but we do read a lot, especially American History that has to do withany<sic>with any</sic> thing Indian, also we buy every book we can about same. we have just read <del><del>t</del><add>T</add>he Shin<del>g</del><add>i</add>n<del>g</del><add>T</add>rail</del>. The Shining Trail. Old Black Hawks war. he was quite a man. There was a little to<sic>too</sic> much fiction in it but it was very good any way I am enclosing a<sic>an</sic> envelope and if you would be so kind as to give me the place where I can get the book and map. We thank you and are waiting for Beechers Island fight now. Old Roman Nose and he was tough. he <del><unclear>oa</unclear></del><add>go</add>t put under in this fight I think. I had it also in my mind that at the wagon Bo<add>x</add> fight was the first time the Remington Breech loader with rolling block wa<add>s</add> used.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Thanking You I remain.</salute>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully.</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John H Miller</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Camdenton.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Mo</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>c/o Ha Ha Tonka</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
